calc.model.visitor

Class OperatorNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • calc.model.visitor.OperatorNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TreeNode

    public class OperatorNode
extends java.lang.Object
implements TreeNode
    A TreeNode in an expression tree is either a leaf or an operator with two children: this is the operator. Its two mandatory children ensure that we can evaluate the operator. Since it can be visited it must have an accept() method - which is of course trivial.
    Author:
    Dave Cohen
